Wheel 0.8.2 aplha release

Content:

src - contains sources for the whole thing
samples - contains a Maven2-based sample application
doc - documentation (a Maven2-generated site, including javadocs)
lib - contains external libraries not available in a public Maven2 repository (namely MVEL)

Where to go from here?

1) Download and install Maven2 if you don't have it yet.
2) Install required dependencies to your local Maven2 repo by running installDependencies.bat (or .sh).
3) Open doc/index.html in your browser or start browsing javadocs by opening doc/apidocs/index.html.
4) Start the samples application and look at the source code for them.